<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101909535094914></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101909535094914><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=631&mid=101909535094914>RE: Lizzard Shadowknight...continues</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=631&mid=101909535094914#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120029><span id=Scholar>Kaellin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>23 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 17th 10:08 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.28]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, it may not be the most exciting story - as you say - but it is certainly intruiging (sp?). It seems that you are building up to something - which I hope is certainly the case - and leaving room for more of the back story to come into play.<br><br>For instance - while Shrikke may be off adventuring like any other EQ toon, he still has a background that haunts him. I wonder - why is the Haggle Baron interested in the vampire? What will the name of the vampire enable the Haggle Baron to do? How will passing this information on affect Shrikke inj times to come?<br><br>Exciting in the sense of conflict and adventure? Maybe not. Exciting in the sense of &quot;Oooo...what's gonna happen&quot;? For sure.<br><br>I'll be coming back :)<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Kaellin Waywatcher - Champion of Faydark</b><br><br><i>"We few, we happy few, we band of brothers; For he to-day that sheds his blood with me shall be my brother" </i>- Henry V, Shakespeare</td></tr>
