	   <tr><td colspan=2>Excellent Sir Parttime.&nbsp;&nbsp;I to play a dwarf paladin on the PVP server Tallon Zek.  What you said about the bad pull is correct.  I suspect that perhaps the players you were grouped with were not high enough level yet to recognize that you were trying to pull the train away from them.  Also, I have hunted Unrest many times, and can tell you that trains from inside have a mind of their own.  Sometimes when you you pull them outside they will run in the opposite direction around the estate to chase you to the zone.  This pathing can cause the train to become larger and more dangerous; or, it can cause it to attack the group you were so valiantly trying to defend.<br><br>What I am trying to say is that Unrest is a dangerous zone where stuff like this happens all the time.  Look at the good side.  You died after using your lay on hands and healing and brawling, allowing most of your party to escape alive.  These are the true actions of a paladin, especially a paladin of Brell.  <br><br>Ironhom Hammerforge<br>Dwarven Paladin<br>Tallon Zek Server<br>Syndicate of Light<br>&nbsp;<br>Ironhom Hammerforge<br>Paladin of Kaladim<br>Chivalric Order<br><br><br><br><br></td></tr>
