	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are correct on a couple of points Shrikke.<br><br>As for some more clarification, there are three distinct factions within Cabilis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Necromancers and the Troopers are allies, the Shadowknights and the Shaman are opposing allies, and the Monks have yet to make a choice in the struggle for dominance.<br><br>As for Mistmoor, yes, we necromancers would ally with him.  Better to be an ally of a vampire than a slave to a dragon, is it not so?<br><br>As for Innoruuk, no, we shall not follow the lord of hate, even though it may promise the children of fear more of benefit...  we are broodlings, and our souls are formed within the plane of Fear.<br><br>As for the Emperor, I have not seen him myself, but I fear what may come out of Karnor's Castle.  We of the necromancers would not be ruled by undead!<br><br>Usula of the Wurmbane clutch<br>Female Hatchling on the Mithaniel Marr Server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
