	   <tr><td colspan=2>To the elf Judd<br><br>Softskin, you need not wish us Luck.&nbsp;&nbsp;We of the Iksar make our own luck... but your observations are correct;  it is better for us to ally ourselves with Mistmoor over the Dragons, but not for the reasons you would assume.<br><br>As an elf, whose primary use in Cabilis is to make Smoked Wood Elf, I think you underestimate the might of our newfound empire.  Regardless of what Pusbag may think (trolls being a bit dillusional and all), we of the BroodofKotiz are masters of death, plague, and disease.  We are further masters of the undead, and have fashioned spells to aid us in their control.  Our monks are the best in all of Norrath simply because Cazic felt it necessary to give us the ability to regenerate our health quickly.  Our warriors, while not able to wear those plates of metal favored by other races, are quite dextrous and strong, and their cunning more than makes up for their discomfort with the plate armor.  And, even though I dislike the shadowknights and shaman of our race, they have powers and are powerful in their own right.  My point, softskin, is that while I believe we would side with Mistmoor in any upcoming conflicts with the dragons, it is not out of fear that we do so.  We are strong enough to withstand Mistmoor, and strong enough to withstand another assault by the cursed dragonkind...  but we think it prudent to ally ourselves with one who has directed efforts against dragonkind in our past... perhaps the old addage of the enemy of my enemy is my friend would apply here.<br><br>Usula, Iksar Necromancer<br>Queen of Fear<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
